♪There's no fruit without flowers♪

755
00:43:10,370 --> 00:43:12,980
♪Or rain without clouds♪

756
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:16,910
♪Or fire without wind♪

757
00:43:18,420 --> 00:43:22,690
♪All are born amid cries♪

758
00:43:23,340 --> 00:43:26,090
♪Everyone laughs and dances♪

759
00:43:26,550 --> 00:43:30,420
♪Each one bound in chains♪

760
00:43:30,600 --> 00:43:32,260
♪Sinner♪

761
00:43:32,680 --> 00:43:35,520
♪The shell that traps you♪

762
00:43:36,230 --> 00:43:39,040
♪Is also gilded♪

763
00:43:39,210 --> 00:43:42,650
♪How could one bear to shed it?♪

764
00:43:43,640 --> 00:43:45,240
♪Sufferer♪

765
00:43:45,630 --> 00:43:49,330
♪Hate is a road with no return♪

766
00:43:49,330 --> 00:43:52,170
♪There's nothing at the end♪

767
00:43:52,360 --> 00:43:56,260
♪Cause and effect trade roles♪

768
00:43:56,590 --> 00:43:58,600
♪Unable to love♪

769
00:43:58,600 --> 00:44:02,840
♪Yet still leap
into pavilions in the air♪

770
00:44:03,030 --> 00:44:04,880
♪Unable to let go♪

771
00:44:05,080 --> 00:44:09,400
♪Still asking why♪

772
00:44:09,550 --> 00:44:11,250
♪Unable to ask♪

773
00:44:11,610 --> 00:44:16,250
♪So you trade everything for nothing♪

774
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:18,070
♪Unwilling to lose♪

775
00:44:18,070 --> 00:44:22,250
♪You err, then err again♪

776
00:44:22,470 --> 00:44:24,580
♪A single person♪

777
00:44:24,580 --> 00:44:29,050
♪Whose cause bore whose fruit♪

778
00:44:29,050 --> 00:44:30,930
♪A single rain♪

779
00:44:30,930 --> 00:44:35,520
♪Cannot wash away good and evil♪

780
00:44:35,520 --> 00:44:37,470
♪One glance back♪

781
00:44:37,470 --> 00:44:42,030
♪Who is not a guest to feast and die♪

782
00:44:42,030 --> 00:44:44,880
♪Only then do we know at the start♪

783
00:44:44,880 --> 00:44:48,200
♪Why people cry♪

784
00:44:48,420 --> 00:44:50,530
♪A single person♪

785
00:44:50,530 --> 00:44:54,750
♪This life has no other river♪

786
00:44:54,950 --> 00:44:57,020
♪A single love♪

787
00:44:57,020 --> 00:45:01,440
♪A wave to the far shore♪

788
00:45:01,440 --> 00:45:03,460
♪One word from me♪

789
00:45:03,460 --> 00:45:07,880
♪Yet I don't know how to say it to you♪

790
00:45:07,880 --> 00:45:10,040
♪Look at those lanterns♪

791
00:45:10,040 --> 00:45:14,070
♪The years locked us in♪

792
00:45:14,290 --> 00:45:16,910
♪Hear the joyous song rise♪

793
00:45:16,910 --> 00:45:23,740
♪The human heart tastes bitter♪
